    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-24T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="395"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93114A/8–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-24T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 24, 1945—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 24—9:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3986. Following telegram from Fontanel. Same official telephones (Legation’s
                    3957, August 22).</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Confirms fear conflict in absence American Forces.</item>
                    <pb facs="0548" n="538" xml:id="pg_538"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Has received reports confirming uneasiness Shanghai. States even small
                        American Force would be sufficient maintain order threatened (repeated
                        Chungking) by native political elements and Communists.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
